  <p>Infonavit reported that the confidence of beneficiaries to acquire a home is recovering side by side
    with country's economic activity, as the Home Purchase Intention Index stood at 36.7 points in 2Q21, 2.5
    points higher than in 1Q21. Likewise, in May, the Institute’s new peso-denominated credit scheme came into
    effect, with fixed interest rate (from 1.91% to 10.45%, depending on the salary registered with the Social
     Security and Welfare Institute) and payments throughout the life of the loan, for the benefit of workers.</p>

  <p>Against this background, the prospects of main housing institutes are positive for the remainder of 2021,
    bearing in mind that during 1H21, Infonavit collected of Ps. 131,210 million from employers, a growth of 6.4%
     compared to the same period of the previous year.</p>

